                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-271-victim2053 t18311201-271-viclabel1442"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18311201-271-crimeloc1443">Little George-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-271-crimeloc1443" type="placeName" value="Little George-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-271-crimeloc1443" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-271-off1440 t18311201-271-crimeloc1443"></join>. The prisoner came this day fortnight to purchase a waistcoat, and I showed him several - he came again on the 2nd of December with a young man; they asked for waistcoats, and I gave each one to try on - my daughter was in the shop; I went out, and when I returned she said to me, "Mother, they have put something into their hats;" I said, "Young men, if you are honest, you will pull off your hats;" the other one ran away, but the prisoner was detained - when the Policeman came he threw down his hat in the shop, and in it was this waistcoat - I believe the other man took one, but I would not swear it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-271-person2055">
